"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-paralympics-kadeena-cox-paris-jackie-chan-france-british-b2604092.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 321, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Kadeena Coxrued a \\\"really rubbish year\\\" after her eight-year reign as Paralympic C4-5 time trial champion ended in frustrating fashion with a crash atParis2024.\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 506, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Britishcyclist Cox, who was second fastest in qualifying behind Caroline Groot, fell on the first corner of her medal race after wobbling following a slow start.\", \"from\": 508, \"to\": 669, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 572, \"end\": 586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caroline_Groot\", \"score\": 0.9999933051532396, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Caroline Groot\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caroline_Groot\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caroline_Groot\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Daphne Schrager and Stephen Bate subsequently secured Britain's maiden podium places inFrancewith silvers at the velodrome.\", \"from\": 671, \"to\": 794, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 671, \"end\": 677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daphne_Blake\", \"score\": 0.999999290936354, \"rank\": 7.090638929564601e-07, \"text\": \"Daphne\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daphne_Blake\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daphne_Blake\"}, {\"begin\": 691, \"end\": 703, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Bate\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stephen Bate\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Bate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Bate\"}, {\"begin\": 725, \"end\": 732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.7758430546206179, \"rank\": 0.288917930273441, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Schrager finished second in the women's C1-3 3000m individual pursuit, while Bate and pilot Chris Latham were runners-up in the men's B 4000m individual pursuit.\", \"from\": 796, \"to\": 957, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 888, \"end\": 900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Latham_(rugby_union)\", \"score\": 0.9409601594669764, \"rank\": 0.05798394290811248, \"text\": \"Chris Latham\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13415036\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Latham_(rugby_union)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Latham_(rugby_union)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Following a series of fitness setbacks, Cox, who has multiple sclerosis, appeared distraught as she hobbled from the track with assistance from members of the ParalympicsGB team.\", \"from\": 959, \"to\": 1137, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think I got back on the bike two weeks ago,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1139, \"to\": 1196, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was in a boot four weeks ago.\", \"from\": 1197, \"to\": 1229, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It has just been a really rubbish year.\", \"from\": 1231, \"to\": 1271, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This time last year I could not walk because I had a really bad relapse that affected my right side.\", \"from\": 1272, \"to\": 1372, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It has been a roller-coaster, I guess that's MS.\", \"from\": 1374, \"to\": 1423, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1420, \"end\": 1423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuscript\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"MS.\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuscript\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuscript\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's just not what you want a year out from the Games.\", \"from\": 1424, \"to\": 1478, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The fact that I got here was amazing in itself - I am just gutted I was able to ride a ride that was pretty great in the first round and then not go out there and show what I am capable of.\\\"\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1671, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Leeds-born Cox was denied a restart as the fall was deemed not to be down to a mechanical fault.\", \"from\": 1673, \"to\": 1769, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She continued to receive treatment on the floor of the track centre long after the event had finished.\", \"from\": 1771, \"to\": 1873, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I overcompensated and just could not balance on my weaker side.\", \"from\": 1875, \"to\": 1938, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was all over the shop.\", \"from\": 1939, \"to\": 1964, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The world record holder had looked odds-on to become GB's first medallist of the Games following her triumphs at Rio 2016 and Tokyo 2020.\", \"from\": 1966, \"to\": 2103, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2019, \"end\": 2021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9707623088384442, \"rank\": 0.02993425133249161, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 2092, \"end\": 2097, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9997376845480924, \"rank\": 0.0002622248569022627, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dutch rider Groot subsequently took the title, ahead of French home favourite Marie Patouillet, with Canadian Kate O'Brien third.\", \"from\": 2105, \"to\": 2234, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2105, \"end\": 2110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"score\": 0.9937080629003192, \"rank\": 0.0037362816690674865, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2117, \"end\": 2122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Groot\", \"score\": 0.9999999762085284, \"rank\": 2.3773354825562023e-08, \"text\": \"Groot\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Groot\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Groot\"}, {\"begin\": 2161, \"end\": 2167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.942539370900468, \"rank\": 0.0458476156766504, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2183, \"end\": 2199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Patouillet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marie Patouillet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Patouillet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Patouillet\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cox is scheduled to race again on Sunday when she defends the C1-5 mixed team sprint title alongside Jody Cundy and Jaco van Gass.\", \"from\": 2236, \"to\": 2366, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2337, \"end\": 2347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jody_Cundy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jody Cundy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jody_Cundy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jody_Cundy\"}, {\"begin\": 2352, \"end\": 2365, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jaco_van_Gass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jaco van Gass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jaco_van_Gass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jaco_van_Gass\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was a weird one - I did not feel comfortable in the gate,\\\" she said of her fall.\", \"from\": 2368, \"to\": 2452, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"My right side is my weak side and with a condition like mine, riding can not always be perfect.\", \"from\": 2454, \"to\": 2550, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I overcompensated and just could not balance on my weaker side.\", \"from\": 2552, \"to\": 2616, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was all over the shop.\\\"\", \"from\": 2617, \"to\": 2643, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Actor and martial artistJackie Chanwas part of the presentation party as Schrager received her landmark medal.\", \"from\": 2645, \"to\": 2755, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 23-year-old, who has cerebral palsy, only joined the cycling programme in 2019, having never previously ridden.\", \"from\": 2757, \"to\": 2872, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She set a C2 world record of 3:45.133 in qualifying before clocking 3:51.129 in the final, just under 10 seconds slower than Chinese gold medallist Xiaomei Wang.\", \"from\": 2874, \"to\": 3035, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2999, \"end\": 3006, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"score\": 0.8926075295312802, \"rank\": 0.11933755118997004, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If you'd asked me a year ago, I would have bitten your arm off to have one,\\\" Schrager said of the medal.\", \"from\": 3037, \"to\": 3142, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I could feel she (Wang) was coming and I knew I did not have any more to give.\", \"from\": 3144, \"to\": 3223, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I gave it everything and I broke my world record in the process, I am so happy I did that.\", \"from\": 3224, \"to\": 3314, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She was just better on the day.\\\"\", \"from\": 3315, \"to\": 3347, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Two-time Paralympic champion Bate celebrated the fifth medal of his Games career.\", \"from\": 3349, \"to\": 3430, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He and Latham were just over two seconds slower than Dutch duo Tristan Bangma and Patrick Bos, who won with a new world record of 3:55.396.\", \"from\": 3432, \"to\": 3571, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3439, \"end\": 3445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swayne_Latham\", \"score\": 0.9989933088850906, \"rank\": 0.0010073871270587455, \"text\": \"Latham\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swayne_Latham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swayne_Latham\"}, {\"begin\": 3485, \"end\": 3490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"score\": 0.9937080629003192, \"rank\": 0.0037362816690674865, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3514, \"end\": 3521, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danica_Patrick\", \"score\": 0.9999996308252548, \"rank\": 3.6491481752247433e-07, \"text\": \"Patrick\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q378622\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danica_Patrick\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danica_Patrick\"}, {\"begin\": 3522, \"end\": 3525, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bos\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bos\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The medal represents nine months of hard graft and a massive team effort,\\\" said 47-year-old Bate.\", \"from\": 3573, \"to\": 3671, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We gave it everything we had to try to beat the Dutch guys but they proved how world class they are.\\\"\", \"from\": 3673, \"to\": 3775, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3722, \"end\": 3727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"score\": 0.9937080629003192, \"rank\": 0.0037362816690674865, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 3777, \"to\": 3913, \"entities\": []}]}"